Structs/Word/PartOfSpeech.html.name: PartOfSpeech
Structs/Word/PartOfSpeech.html.abstract: Japanese only.** The part of speech for the word. The service uses the value to produce the correct intonation for the word. You can create only a single entry, with or without a single part of speech, for any word; you cannot create multiple entries with different parts of speech for the same word. For more information, see Working with Japanese entries.

Structs/Word.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14Wo.name: word
Structs/Word.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14Wo.abstract: A word from the custom voice model.

Structs/Word.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14Wo.name: translation
Structs/Word.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14Wo.abstract: The phonetic or sounds-like translation for the word. A phonetic translation is based on the SSML format for representing the phonetic string of a word either as an IPA or IBM SPR translation. A sounds-like translation consists of one or more words that, when combined, sound like the word.

Structs/Word.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14Wo.name: partOfSpeech
Structs/Word.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14Wo.abstract: Japanese only.** The part of speech for the word. The service uses the value to produce the correct intonation for the word. You can create only a single entry, with or without a single part of speech, for any word; you cannot create multiple entries with different parts of speech for the same word. For more information, see Working with Japanese entries.

Structs/Translation/PartOfSpeech.html.name: PartOfSpeech
Structs/Translation/PartOfSpeech.html.abstract: Japanese only.** The part of speech for the word. The service uses the value to produce the correct intonation for the word. You can create only a single entry, with or without a single part of speech, for any word; you cannot create multiple entries with different parts of speech for the same word. For more information, see Working with Japanese entries.

Structs/Translation.html#/s:14TextToSpee.name: translation
Structs/Translation.html#/s:14TextToSpee.abstract: The phonetic or sounds-like translation for the word. A phonetic translation is based on the SSML format for representing the phonetic string of a word either as an IPA translation or as an IBM SPR translation. A sounds-like is one or more words that, when combined, sound like the word.

Structs/Translation.html#/s:14TextToSpee.name: partOfSpeech
Structs/Translation.html#/s:14TextToSpee.abstract: Japanese only.** The part of speech for the word. The service uses the value to produce the correct intonation for the word. You can create only a single entry, with or without a single part of speech, for any word; you cannot create multiple entries with different parts of speech for the same word. For more information, see Working with Japanese entries.

Structs/Voice.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15V.name: name
Structs/Voice.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15V.abstract: The name of the voice. Use this as the voice identifier in all requests.

Structs/Voice.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15V.name: language
Structs/Voice.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15V.abstract: The language and region of the voice (for example, en-US).

Structs/Voice.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15V.name: customizable
Structs/Voice.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15V.abstract: If true, the voice can be customized; if false, the voice cannot be customized. (Same as custom_pronunciation; maintained for backward compatibility.).

Structs/Voice.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15V.name: supportedFeatures
Structs/Voice.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15V.abstract: Describes the additional service features supported with the voice.

Structs/Voice.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15V.name: customization
Structs/Voice.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15V.abstract: Returns information about a specified custom voice model. Note: This field is returned only when you list information about a specific voice and specify the GUID of a custom voice model that is based on that voice.

Structs/CreateVoiceModel/Language.html.name: Language
Structs/CreateVoiceModel/Language.html.abstract: The language of the new custom voice model. Omit the parameter to use the the default language, en-US.

Structs/CreateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.name: name
Structs/CreateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.abstract: The name of the new custom voice model.

Structs/CreateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.name: language
Structs/CreateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.abstract: The language of the new custom voice model. Omit the parameter to use the the default language, en-US.

Structs/CreateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.name: description
Structs/CreateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.abstract: A description of the new custom voice model. Specifying a description is recommended.

Structs/SupportedFeatures.html#/s:14Text.name: customPronunciation
Structs/SupportedFeatures.html#/s:14Text.abstract: If true, the voice can be customized; if false, the voice cannot be customized. (Same as customizable.).

Structs/SupportedFeatures.html#/s:14Text.name: voiceTransformation
Structs/SupportedFeatures.html#/s:14Text.abstract: If true, the voice can be transformed by using the SSML <voice-transformation> element; if false, the voice cannot be transformed.

Structs/UpdateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.name: name
Structs/UpdateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.abstract: A new name for the custom voice model.

Structs/UpdateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.name: description
Structs/UpdateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.abstract: A new description for the custom voice model.

Structs/UpdateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.name: words
Structs/UpdateVoiceModel.html#/s:14TextT.abstract: An array of words and their translations that are to be added or updated for the custom voice model. Pass an empty array to make no additions or updates.

Structs/Words.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15W.name: words
Structs/Words.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV15W.abstract: An array of words and their translations from the custom voice model. The words are listed in alphabetical order, with uppercase letters listed before lowercase letters. The array is empty if the custom model contains no words.

Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.name: customizationID
Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.abstract: The customization ID (GUID) of the custom voice model. Note: When you create a new custom voice model, the service returns only the GUID of the new custom model; it does not return the other fields of this object.

Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.name: name
Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.abstract: The name of the custom voice model.

Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.name: language
Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.abstract: The language identifier of the custom voice model (for example, en-US).

Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.name: owner
Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.abstract: The GUID of the service credentials for the instance of the service that owns the custom voice model.

Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.name: created
Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.abstract: The date and time in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) at which the custom voice model was created. The value is provided in full ISO 8601 format (YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sTZD).

Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.name: lastModified
Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.abstract: The date and time in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) at which the custom voice model was last modified. Equals created when a new voice model is first added but has yet to be updated. The value is provided in full ISO 8601 format (YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sTZD).

Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.name: description
Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.abstract: The description of the custom voice model.

Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.name: words
Structs/VoiceModel.html#/s:14TextToSpeec.abstract: An array of words and their translations from the custom voice model. The words are listed in alphabetical order, with uppercase letters listed before lowercase letters. The array is empty if the custom model contains no words. Note: This field is returned only when you list information about a specific custom voice model.

Structs/VoiceModels.html#/s:14TextToSpee.name: customizations
Structs/VoiceModels.html#/s:14TextToSpee.abstract: An array of VoiceModel objects that provides information about each available custom voice model. The array is empty if the requesting service credentials own no custom voice models (if no language is specified) or own no custom voice models for the specified language.

Structs/Pronunciation.html#/s:14TextToSp.name: pronunciation
Structs/Pronunciation.html#/s:14TextToSp.abstract: The pronunciation of the requested text in the specified voice and format.

Structs.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV111JSONWr.name: JSONWrapper
Structs.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV111JSONWr.abstract: Used internally to serialize and deserialize JSON.

Enums/JSON.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14JSON.name: double
Enums/JSON.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14JSON.abstract: A number value, represented as a double.

Enums/JSON.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14JSON.name: init(from:)
Enums/JSON.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14JSON.abstract: Initialize a JSON value from an encodable type.

Enums/JSON.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14JSON.name: toValue(_:)
Enums/JSON.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV14JSON.abstract: Convert this JSON value to a decodable type.

Enums/RestError.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV1.name: noResponse
Enums/RestError.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV1.abstract: No response was received from the server.

Enums/RestError.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV1.name: noData
Enums/RestError.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV1.abstract: No data was returned from the server.

Enums/RestError.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV1.name: encodingError
Enums/RestError.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV1.abstract: Failed to replace special characters in the

Enums/RestError.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV1.name: fileManagerError
Enums/RestError.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV1.abstract: FileManager failed to handle the given file.

Enums/RestError.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV1.name: failure
Enums/RestError.html#/s:14TextToSpeechV1.abstract: An HTTP error with a status code and description.

Enums/RestError.html.name: RestError
Enums/RestError.html.abstract: An error from processing a network request or response.

Enums/JSON.html.name: JSON
Enums/JSON.html.abstract: A JSON value (one of string, number, object, array, true, false, or null).

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: serviceURL
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: The base URL to use when contacting the service.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: defaultHeaders
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: The default HTTP headers for all requests to the service.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Retrieves a specific voice available for speech synthesis.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: listVoices(failure:success:)
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Retrieves all voices available for speech synthesis.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: synthesize(text:accept:voice:customizationID:failure:success:)
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Streaming speech synthesis of the text in the body parameter.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: getVoiceModel(customizationID:failure:success:)
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Queries the contents of a custom voice model.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: listVoiceModels(language:failure:success:)
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Lists all available custom voice models for a language or for all languages.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: updateVoiceModel(customizationID:name:description:words:failure:success:)
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Updates information and words for a custom voice model.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: addWord(customizationID:word:translation:partOfSpeech:failure:success:)
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Adds a word to a custom voice model.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: addWords(customizationID:words:failure:success:)
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Adds one or more words to a custom voice model.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: deleteWord(customizationID:word:failure:success:)
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Deletes a word from a custom voice model.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: getWord(customizationID:word:failure:success:)
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Queries details about a word in a custom voice model.

Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.name: listWords(customizationID:failure:success:)
Classes/TextToSpeech.html#/s:14TextToSpe.abstract: Queries details about the words in a custom voice model.
